{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2016}} {{original research|date=August 2016}} {{more footnotes|date=July 2016}} {{Infobox language |name= Are bashe |nativename=ಅರೆಭಾಷೆ |states=[[India]] |region=[[Kodagu]], [[Dakshina Kannada]] [[Kasaragod district|Kasaragodu]] |ethnicity=[[Kodagu_Gowda]] |speakers = |ref= |date=2011 |familycolor=Dravidian |fam2=[[Southern Dravidian languages|Southern]] family |fam3=[[Kannada]] languages |fam5=Kodagu |script=[[Kannada script]] |glotto= |isoexception=dialect }}
'''Arebhashe''' is a [[dialect]] of [[Kannada language|Kannada]] spoke by [[Hindu|Hindus]] of the [[Kodagu gowdas|Gowda]]<ref name="kdkgowdas.com">{{cite web|url=http://www.kdkgowdas.com/|title=Kdk|author=|date=|work=kdkgowdas.com}}</ref> community in the regions of [[Kodagu district|Kodagu]] and [[Sullia]] of [[Dakshina Kannada]] in the Indian state of [[Karnataka]]..
==Etymology== Linguists<ref>[[:kn:ಪುರುಷೋತ್ತಮ ಬಿಳಿಮಲೆ]]</ref> have suggested that the word Arebhashe means 'half-tongue,' from the Arebhashe word "a're" meaning "half" and ''bhashe,'' meaning "speech." Arebhashe pronunciation and accent are slightly distinct from [[Kannada language|Kannada]].
==History== Arebhashe is written in the Kannada script.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sharedlist.org/writing/Arebhashe%20or%20Gowda%20Kannada%20is%20a%20dialect%20of%20the%20Kannada%20language-589/?i=9450|title=Arebhashe|last=|first=|date=|publisher=|access-date=|author=|work=arebhase.blogspot.in}}</ref>The Arebhashe dialect is believed to have originated during the transformation of Hale Kannada to Hosa Kannada, and according to some historians{{who|date=June 2018}} the dialect may be five-hundred years old.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.coorga2z.in/regional/kodagu-arebhashe-gowdas-ethnic-group|title=Kodagu Arebhashe Gowdas - A Ethnic Group - Coorg A2Z|author=|date=24 September 2015|work=coorga2z.in}}</ref>{{better source|date=August 2016}}
