{{Infobox language |name=Bantang |nativename= |states=[[Laos]] |region= |ethnicity= |speakers= unknown |date= |ref= |familycolor=Sino-Tibetan |fam2=([[Tibeto-Burman languages|Tibeto-Burman]]) |fam3=[[Lolo–Burmese languages|Lolo–Burmese]] |fam4=[[Loloish languages|Loloish]] |fam5=[[Southern Loloish languages|Southern]] |fam6=[[Bisoid languages|Bisoid]] |iso3=none |glotto=bant1298 |glottorefname=Bantang }}
'''Bantang''' (autonym: ''ban˧taŋ˧'') is a [[Loloish language]] of northern [[Laos]]. It is divergent with the Bisoid (Phunoi) branch.
