The '''Netherlands Mycological Society''' (Dutch: ''Nederlandse Mycologische Vereniging'' (NMV)) is the national [[learned society|society]] for the Netherlands promoting the study of [[fungi]]. It was founded in 1908 and currently has around 800 members. It publishes the [[scientific journal|journal]] ''Coolia'' as well as various other ad hoc publications, and organises national meetings, courses and mycological excursions.<ref>[http://www.mycologen.nl/nmv_e.htm Nederlandse Mycologische Vereniging (Netherlands Mycological Society) Website] (Accessed Jan 2011)</ref>
The society is part of the Pan-European Species directories Infrastructure (PESI).<ref>[http://www.eu-nomen.eu/pesi/index.php?option=com_imis&Itemid=55&module=institute&insid=11304 Pan-European Species directories Infrastructure (PESI)] (Accessed Jan 2011)</ref> == References == {{Reflist}} [[Category:Mycology organizations]] [[Category:1908 establishments in the Netherlands]] [[Category:Clubs and societies in the Netherlands]] [[Category:Scientific organizations established in 1908]] [[Category:Scientific organisations based in the Netherlands]]
